snippet.textDisplay:
Hey, Doctor Mike, I have a question for you that I hope you are able to answer. Before I get to the question, let me give you a piece of history relating to it first. When I was in high school and carrying my cell phone in my purse, I used to have the phone on vibrate all the time. I'm more comfortable carrying my purse over my head and on my right shoulder, so the strap tends to go across my chest in the process of it hanging by my left hip. The irony is that I never once felt my phone vibrate when it was on me, but one day I felt my right breast vibrate and immediately checked my phone to see if I was receiving a phone call, text, or notification, but there was nothing on the screen when I looked. I don't remember exactly when this happened, I just know that I was at the mall relaxing at the time. However, ever since that day, I've been feeling my chest vibrate from time to time, and it always seems to only happen in the summer. Occasionally it happens during the winter, but it's always the summer for the most part. It's usually my right breast that vibrates, but sometimes the left one does too.

Anyway, now that I've given you the back story of why my chest vibrates sometimes, here are my questions. Is it normal for a woman's breasts to vibrate? For that matter, is it normal for anyone's chest to vibrate at all? I've been curious about this for a while, but I keep forgetting to talk to my doctor about it during my appointments.

Dr Mike
I have a very hard question because I have asked over 50 doctors with no answer so maybe you can help.

“What is wrong with me and how can we stop the pain/ symptoms/ spasms/ seizures/ fatigue/ fever/ etc.”

I was an emergency c-section baby in fetal distress born 2 months earlier yet only developed as of 3 months premature. I have a very rare Partial chromosome deletion that kills most babies in the womb, which is why I’m so rare to be 28 with my condition.

But none of that explains my issues/ symptoms. I have been unable to work for almost a year now because it’s gotten so bad that I’m into much pain and I need supervision. As of last summer I was no longer even allowed to live on my own in case I have a medical issue and so 28th I had to move back in with my parents. My entire life we have been seeing doctor after doctor and specialists after specialist. And have been turned away by many doctors, Because they don’t know how to help me but no there’s something wrong but there’s nothing else they can do. This happened again last Monday. I am getting desperate. And I need a doctor to help me. But right now All they can do is give me meds To help the symptoms not the issue. I have to be taking Oxy Multiple times a day for two years. And multiple Strong muscle relaxers multiple times a day for over two years probably over three. I eat one meal a day to meals if I can manage due to all the pain and nausea. I know you’re not the Doctor Who can help me But I’m putting it out there because I’m desperate just tired of being sick and tired of being a burden and I’m tired of going to doctors appointments and therapy every week multiple times a week. I need help and I don’t want to continue taking all of these medications. I am taking large amounts of opioids and I’m not addicted but I’ve seen what it is done to people in my family and my uncle was killed by the police because of those addictions. I don’t want to be another person in the opioid crisis But I don’t want to be in pain either. I don’t want to sit at home playing video games and watching YouTube all day. I want to work I want to life I want to be able to take my service dog on a daily walk or to the park, Instead of paying my little sister to. I need help from the doctor. I need answers And I am desperate for those answers and I’m sick and tired of being turned away from doctors because they can’t help me. Please help me please.
